summary: Back in 2015, I met my ultimate bestfriend, Puteri during the first day of orientation for our foundation, and I literally...
body: Back in 2015, I met my ultimate bestfriend, Puteri during the first day of orientation for our foundation, and I literally started the conversation with her just by saying “Omg, hi I’m Nina, you like Taylor Swift too??!!” because I saw her lockscreen was of Taylor, and I asked her on whether she went to the Red tour back in Malaysia, and she did and we could’ve met way before and we just clicked & now we’re the best of friends, and we even tried to win tickets for her 1989 tour in Singapore but we failed because it was sold out and to enter a competition was our only hope but sadly we didn’t make it, but now, today, this year in 2018, I got a surprise from my boyfriend and friends which are TICKETS TO HER REPUTATION STADIUM TOUR IN SYDNEY THIS UPCOMING NOVEMBER, and I got to surprise Puteri with one of her own tickets as well with one of our other bestfriend, and we just got our flight tickets & booked a place to stay in Sydney for 5 days & omg I’m freaking out but we’re meeting Taylor again and eventhough we didn’t get front seats because it’s too expensive for us, I’m just glad we’re going to experience the MOST ANTICIPATING TOUR YET, & I can’t wait till this November, and Taylor if you’re ever reading this. We love you so much, and thank you, for building this friendship for us, and thank you, for all the songs you’ve created that helped us through our bad days or even help us enjoy our happy days because of how relatable it is. I’m looking forward to see you this November 😭❤️ So much love! We’re coming 4144 miles all the way for you! I hope that shows how much we really love you! Help reblog this so Taylor can see 💘 #ReputationStadiumTourSydney, Category D, Section S628-2, Row 40, Seats 5-6
